(1, 'Account Executive Marketing', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0', '', 599683, '', 'both', '', '', '<p align=\"center\"><b>Commercial Account Executive Job Summary</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>The Account Executive Managers&#39; main functions are customer service and following the Account CRM. &nbsp;&nbsp;They are the agency&#39;s primary visible service arm to provide the day-to-day supervision over the coordination and execution of all facets of both the Account Service Plan and routine in-house transactions. The Account Manager is also responsible for the renewal processes including the professional marketing of the clients&#39; insurance programs. &nbsp;In all areas, it is expected that the Account Manager will actively seek to cultivate, improve and cement a positive client relationship. &nbsp;The Account Manager may utilize the support of the Account Analyst when performing these functions.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Directly Reports:&nbsp; Principle/Large Accounts Producer </b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><u>Primary Responsibilities for Commercial Insurance Account Executive </u></b></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><b>Prepares and maintains summaries of insurance, schedules, files, proposals and updates client notebooks as needed for new and renewal accounts.</b></li>\r\n	<li><b>Markets renewals, contacts clients, creates renewal proposals and handles other renewal activities independently or in coordination with the Account Executive or Producer.</b></li>\r\n	<li><b>Renews policies following agency timing and quality standards. After the Account Analyst has completed the initial review of the policies, the Account Manager gives the policies a final check and completes a risk management report before sending out the insured&#39;s copies of the policies.&nbsp; </b></li>\r\n	<li><b>As needed performs rating plan analyses, quote comparisons, and other analytical functions.</b></li>\r\n	<li><b>Reviews contracts for clients as requested.</b></li>\r\n	<li><b>Handles client policy change requests and needs throughout policy year, including company contact, endorsement requests and follow-ups and their review. </b></li>\r\n	<li><b>Manage team including but not limited to:</b></li>\r\n	<li><b>Supervising the Account Analyst</b></li>\r\n	<li><b>Managing the daily Account Handling system - renewals, marketing, etc.</b></li>\r\n	<li><b>&nbsp;Managing the service plan created by the Producer</b></li>\r\n	<li><b>&nbsp;Proactively and independently resolves client problems.</b></li>\r\n	<li><b>&nbsp;&nbsp;Responsible for having the Commercial Lines Assistant review the WC experience </b></li>\r\n	<li><b>&nbsp;modifications for accuracy of data and classifications.</b></li>\r\n	<li><b>&nbsp;Verifies accuracy of all client audits and requests corrections as necessary.</b></li>\r\n	<li><b>&nbsp;Documents all customer service transactions including but not limited to phone conversations and the processing of daily work via TAM AND AMS 360 software</b></li>\r\n	<li><b>Uses agency credit and collection policy in invoicing and pursuing prompt payments.</b></li>\r\n	<li><b>Processes and follows up on cancellation requests to carriers to ensure accurate and timely resolution; maintains agency in financial equity whenever possible.</b></li>\r\n	<li><b>Implements and applies the agency performance review system justly, consistently and in accordance with agency timing standards. &nbsp;Actively participates in and supports the training endeavors of the agency.</b></li>\r\n	<li><b>Assists and completes other tasks as directed by agency management.</b></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><b><u>Job Accountability Measures</u></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Customer satisfaction; retention</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Adherence to established procedures</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Timing and quality of service</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Technical accuracy; attention to detail</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Positive professional attitude; leadership</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Proactive problem-solving</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Effective communication</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Personal development</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><u>Personal and Organizational Development</u></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Set priorities and manage work flow to ensure efficient, timely and accurate processing </b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>of transactions and other responsibilities.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Cultivate and maintain a cordial and effective relationship with clients, co-workers, carriers, vendors and other business contacts.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Keep informed regarding industry information, new product information, legislation, coverages and technology to continuously improve knowledge and performance.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Interact with others effectively by utilizing good communications skills, cooperating purposefully and providing information and guidance, as needed, to achieve the business goals of the agency.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Develop leadership managerial skill set appropriate for fulfillment of responsibilities in a team setting.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Knowledge, Skills and Abilities</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;College education or equivalent insurance experience and required </b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Georgia Property &amp; Casualty Insurance Agent&#39;s License.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ability to consistently display a proactive, positive, customer focus and demonstrate a dedicated sense of urgency in serving their interests.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ability to communicate orally and in writing with others to explain issues, receive and interpret information, and respond appropriately.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In-depth knowledge of insurance products and usage; knowledge of insurance markets and reference to markets; knowledge of insurance rating, rating plan and underwriting procedures. &nbsp;Ability to effectively organize, present and negotiate marketing approaches with markets.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ability to carry out complex tasks with many concrete and abstract variables.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Understanding of agency work flow procedures, underwriting and sales and service processes with growing understanding of computer applications to workflow and quality control.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ability to supervise changing workflow priorities for self and direct reports.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ability to utilize computer programs and understand functionality; develop and utilize spreadsheet applications.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Working Conditions</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;High-pressured, fast-paced environment with significant telephone and personal disruption. &nbsp;Large number of multiple steps in complex system performed with accuracy and speed is essential to the successful completion of tasks.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>&nbsp;Benefits: Comprehensive</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Salary Commensurate with experience (above market) &nbsp;</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Location; Vinings, Georgia </b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>This description is intended to describe the general level of work required by the person performing the work. &nbsp;This description is not intended as a contract and is subject to change. &nbsp;Any written contractual agreements supersede this job description. &nbsp;All requirements may be reasonably modified to accommodate physically or mentally challenged employees.</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><u>Employer is an Equal Opportunity Employer</u></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Commercial Insurance Account Executive \r\n', 80414, 0, '0', '0', '', '', 0, '2018-09-10 10:36:48', 0, 262, 356),
(2, 'Commercial Lines CSR', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0', '', 956864, '', 'both', '', '', '<p><b>Commercial Lines CSR </b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Duties</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The CSR provides support to the Commercial Account Manager unit by clearing submissions, handling endorsements, producing account Confirmation of Coverage, clearing new business, soliciting renewals, soliciting new business, setting-up, releasing and following-up on submissions and quotes and other functions as needed</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In this role, you will have the opportunity to process new business, renewals and endorsements for assigned accounts, communicate with team members and outside distributors regarding needs and account changes, maintain logs, monthly report data, record of losses, endorsements and other pertinent information.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Processing includes accurately entering all risk and exposure data into the system and following-up on binder subjectivities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>*Additional skills preferred:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>*Ability to assist Business Owners Policy Policies small to medium-sized markets</p>\r\n\r\n<p>*Ability to assist property market</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Qualifications</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Georgia Property and Casualty Insurance License</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One to two years&rsquo; commercial lines experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>High School diploma required, bachelor&rsquo;s degree preferred.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Salary: Commensurate with Experience&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Location:&nbsp; Gwinnett County&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Benefits Comprehensive&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Commercial Insurance, Administrative, Marketing assistance ', 87278, 0, '0', '0', '', '', 0, '2018-09-10 10:36:48', 0, 798, 354),
(3, 'Commercial LInes Account Manager', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0', '', 2000002, '', 'both', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;This position will have a desk of small to Medium-sized business owner policies.&nbsp; He/She will work directly with insured and producer.&nbsp; This position will know coverage for property and casualty commercial business insurance and can provide the insured with advice and expertise on what is best for their needs.&nbsp; They also can do the marketing and renewal/retention.&nbsp; This position has a high degree of responsibility.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Specific Duties Required</b>:&nbsp; Daily service work on computer and phone.&nbsp; Technical assistance is provided however, you will be responsible for making sure the following is maintained for your clients:&nbsp; The desk is kept current, all changes to accounts are processed in a timely fashion, reports and spreadsheets are current, diary notes entered on the account, a sense of urgency during renewal time, records kept of conversations with producers, account assistants, any person who has any responsibility for the desk.&nbsp; The accounts on this desk will have a range of small to medium-sized markets. &nbsp;&nbsp;Product knowledge includes but not limited to the following:&nbsp; Mix of small to mid-level business owners&rsquo; policy and package accounts.&nbsp; The smaller accounts can have a significant amount of processes and maintenance.&nbsp; Software expertise AMS360</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Interpersonal Skills Required</b>:&nbsp;&nbsp; Exceptional interpersonal skills are required.&nbsp; Excellent phone and computer etiquette, concern for the clients business needs, flexibility, compassion, attention to detail, an overall care and concern for your position and employer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There may be additional duties depending on the particular book of business. If this is the case the interview process will reveal any additional duties or concerns.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>REQUIRED:&nbsp; Georgia Property and Casualty Insurance Agents License</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Salary: Commensurate with experience</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Benefits:&nbsp; Comprehensive&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Location:&nbsp; Gwinnett County Georgia</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As part of our hiring process, candidates must also pass a comprehensive background check and additional screening for credit, Drug or MVR may be required for some positions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Client National is an Equal Opportunity Employer.</p>\r\n', 'Commercial Insurance Account Manager , small to mid-level accounts, marketing accounts, ', 87278, 0, '0', '0', '', '', 0, '2018-09-10 10:36:48', 0, 798, 355),
(4, 'Sales Agent', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '36000', '', 648499, '', 'both', '', '', '<p align=\"center\"><b>Commercial Property and Casualty Insurance Producer/Sales </b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our client has an open position for a motivated individual to provide consultative selling and service of property and casualty commercial insurance products to new and existing clients. More specifically, we are looking for someone to produce business using their prior sales experience in Outside Sales, Door to Door Sales, Phone Sales, Inside Sales or was a Sales Leader at another Insurance agency.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><u>About Client:&nbsp; </u></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our client is a full service P &amp; C Insurance Agency representing insurance carriers that are A-&nbsp; rated by A. M. Best &amp; Co. Our insurance agency prides itself on its service and each client receives a primary agent and a backup agent so that any insurance claims or requests can be serviced quickly and efficiently for the client.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our insurance agency has over 40 years of cumulative agent experience and can offer local insurance expertise in homeowner&rsquo;s, auto, motorcycle, motor home, umbrella, renters, investment property, and commercial coverages in Alpharetta GA, Roswell GA, Johns Creek GA, Marietta GA, Duluth GA, Lilburn GA and Metro Atlanta Georgia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>COMMERCIAL INSURANCE: Just a few examples of our partners:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Allied Insurance</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Amtrust</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ASI</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Auto-Owners Insurance</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Berhshire Hathaway</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Columbia Insurance Group</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Encompass</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Foremost</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Grange Insurance</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mercury Insurance</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Main Street American Group</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Progressive</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Safeco Insurance</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SouthernTrust</p>\r\n\r\n<p>State Auto Insurance Companies</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Travelers</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;<b><u>Professional Experience Required </u></b></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Insurance Sales Experience expected</li>\r\n	<li>Minimum of 2 years of Sales experience required</li>\r\n	<li><b>Property &amp; Casualty Insurance License is required</b>.</li>\r\n	<li>Interest in marketing Property &amp; Casualty Insurance products and services based on customer needs</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to work independently in a professional environment</li>\r\n	<li>Be enthusiastic about the role that insurance products play in client&rsquo;s everyday lives.</li>\r\n	<li>Should have effective presentation skills through both written and verbal communications.</li>\r\n	<li>Should be an assertive self-starter, able to influence others.</li>\r\n	<li>Excellent communication skills, written, verbal, and listening.</li>\r\n	<li>Property &amp; Casualty Insurance Sales Responsibilities:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><b><u>Skillset </u></b></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Develop leads, schedule appointments, identify the business owner&rsquo;s needs, market and quote the appropriate products.</li>\r\n	<li>Establish client relationships through follow-up visits.</li>\r\n	<li>Provide prompt, accurate, and friendly customer service, including response to specific inquiries regarding insurance eligibility, coverages, policy changes, claims and billing.</li>\r\n	<li>Maintain a strong work ethic with a commitment to success each and every day.<br />\r\n	If you are motivated to succeed and can see yourself in this role, please respond</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;immediately. We will follow up with you quickly to begin the next steps in the interview process.</li>\r\n	<li>Permanent Full Time</li>\r\n	<li>Compensation is base salary plus commissions</li>\r\n	<li>Location Suwanee, Georgia</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Salary: Base with generous commission structure</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Benefits: Comprehensive</p>\r\n', 'Property and Casualty Georgia Agents License. Insurance Sales', 64318, 0, '0', '0', '', '', 0, '2018-09-10 10:36:48', 0, 737, 351),
(5, 'EPL & D&O Claims Counsel', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0', '', 648496, '', 'both', '', '', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\"><b>JOB DESCRIPTION EPL &amp; D&amp;O claims Counsel</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Position Type: Temporary Position (duration is open ended)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nThe primary role of Claims Counsel is to analyze liability claim submissions for potential coverage, set adequate case reserves, promptly and professionally respond to inquiries from our clients and their brokers, and to proactively drive early resolution of claims arising from our Executive Risks products, with a focus on D&amp;O and Employment Practices Liability coverage.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nClaims Counsel will manage a full pending of Directors &amp; Officers and Employment Practices Liability matters, as well as provide thought leadership in multiple forums within and outside of the company. Claims Counsel will actively engage in business development, product innovation, and market/customer insight and develop strong working relationships with team members and underwriting leadership.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis is a newly allocated role. It is a fantastic opportunity to join Client, &nbsp;a growing business where you will be able to make a real impact. Together, we aim to be the best people producing the best insurance solutions and delivering the best service possible.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<b>Key Responsibilities:</b></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Strategize with Insured&rsquo;s and Defense Counsel to maximize early settlement opportunities for D&amp;O and Employment Practices Liability matters.</li>\r\n	<li>Analyze and draft coverage analyses</li>\r\n	<li>Monitor underlying negotiations/litigation and manage defense counsel and costs.</li>\r\n	<li>Continually assess exposures and adequacy of claims reserves</li>\r\n	<li>Drive employee engagement by exhibiting passion about the company, values, business and our customers</li>\r\n	<li>Attend mediations and/or settlement conferences where appropriate; travel as required</li>\r\n	<li>Assists in preparing quarterly reserving packs</li>\r\n	<li>Actively participate in the Claims/UW feedback loop</li>\r\n	<li>Keep senior claims management adequately and appropriately informed of key claims and issues</li>\r\n	<li>Liaison directly with insured&rsquo;s and brokers on a daily basis</li>\r\n	<li>Maintain timely and accurate file documentation/information</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Person Specification<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<b>Requirements:</b></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Minimum of 3 years D&amp;O coverage experience</li>\r\n	<li>JD from an ABA-accredited law school &ndash; and or Claims Designations/Senior experience</li>\r\n	<li>Bar admission in good standing &ndash; Preferred but will consider Senior skill set</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to manage case load independently and meet time lines.</li>\r\n	<li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills</li>\r\n	<li>Strong ability to establish rapport and build relationships with clients and internal stakeholders</li>\r\n	<li>Team-oriented, with ability to excel in a collegial environment</li>\r\n	<li>Leadership and people management skills</li>\r\n	<li>Travel as required for mediations, broker and industry meetings</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Location:&nbsp; Atlanta, Georgia</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'EPL (Employment Practices Liability) and D&O (Directors and Officers claims counsel or handeling ', 82763, 0, '0', '0', '', '', 0, '2018-09-10 10:36:48', 0, 1040, 349),
(6, 'Personal Lines Account Manager', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0', '', 0, '', 'both', '', '', '<div>\r\n<p>Personal Lines Account Manager Job Description</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>R</b><b>e</b><b>p</b><b>orts To: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </b>Personal Lines Department</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>S</b><b>t</b><b>a</b><b>t</b><b>u</b><b>s: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </b>Salaried Non-Exempt</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>J</b><b>ob Summary: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </b>The Personal Lines Account Manager works closely with Producers, Carriers, and Client to perform the day-to-day maintenance and servicing of assigned accounts as well as grow their book of business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Location: &nbsp;Atlanta, Georgia</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Pr</b><b>i</b><b>m</b><b>a</b><b>ry Responsibilities:</b></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>STANDARD AND HIGH NET WORTH PERSONAL LINES</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&middot; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Support agency sales efforts by developing complete submissions on new and renewal business and obtain quotes in conjunction with agency marketing procedures</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&middot; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Achieve agency account retention goals through proactive account rounding, and up - selling of limits and coverages.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&middot; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Perform annual review and risk exposure analysis of renewal policies for proper coverage, incorporating information obtained from client and/or Producer</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&middot; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain client files and ensure proper documentation, by processing all policies, endorsement changes, invoices, binders, certificates of insurance, documentation, activities, etc., according to agency procedures, and within agency timelines</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&middot; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintain control of renewal expiration lists, binders, audits, and aged receivables in accordance with agency guidelines</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&middot; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Respond to client inquiries, incoming e-mail, mail, and company requests in accordance with agency guidelines</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&middot; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Review all items to be processed, to insure items were received as ordered</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&middot; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participate in any special projects at management&rsquo;s request</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>P</b><b>e</b><b>r</b><b>so</b><b>na</b><b>l and Organizational Development:</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&middot; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Sets priorities and manages work flow to ensure efficient, timely and accurate processing of transactions and other responsibilities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&middot; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Maintains a cordial and effective relationship with clients, co -workers, carriers, vendors and other business contacts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&middot; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Participate in courses for insurance/sales skills. &nbsp;Maintain current knowledge of underwriting requirements of carriers. &nbsp;Keep current with industry trends by reading appropriate journals and company bulletins.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&middot; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Interacts with others effectively by utilizing good communications skills, cooperating purposefully and providing information and guidance, as needed, to achieve the business goals of the agency.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Personal Lines, high net worth, standard, account service work', 82782, 0, '0', '0', '', '', 0, '2018-09-10 10:36:48', 0, 264, 348),
(7, 'Project Coordinator', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0', '', 582069, '', 'both', '', '', '<p><b>Client Job Summary</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Key Responsibilities / Job Description</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>What you&rsquo;ll need to win</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We&rsquo;re looking for a superstar. Someone who can save the day when disaster strikes. A person who&rsquo;s passionate about bringing calm to chaotic situations, while remaining energetic and devoted to making those affected whole again. A knight in shining armor, always a selfless servant, that is patient and empathetic with clients who could be having the worst day of their year during a devastating event such as a loss. If this is you, you&rsquo;ve come to the right place.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>A typical day may include</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A Client Project Coordinator is a hero in our client&#39;s eyes, articulating and coordinating the information from the field to their dinner table. It&rsquo;s a shoulder to cry on, lending an ear to listen to frustrations, and being the guide who educates through a very complex journey of deductibles and claims. Your work ensures we can solve the difficult problems as a team and move forward together on projects.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A majority of this work is performed during normal business hours. On any given day, you may find yourself preparing project updates, interfacing with clients and business professionals in the industry, and working with a fabulously dynamic team in one of the most fast-paced markets in the Southeast. Most of your projects will occur in commercial and high-rise residential properties across the city.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If this sounds like you, read on. If not, please share it with someone who might be interested.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Skills / Desired Skills and Experience</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>The job might be for your if</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Helping others is who you are - it&rsquo;s in your DNA. You&rsquo;re incredibly patient, level-headed, and cool under pressure. You can explain just about anything to anyone - even when they&rsquo;re in a state of panic.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You are relentless when it comes to wowing customers and exceeding their needs. You have the bedside manner to tactfully tell people what they need to hear and the discernment on when best to do so.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You enjoy difficult challenges and finding creative solutions. You don&rsquo;t get flustered easily but expect there to be times of great frustration. You are sensitive and empathetic to the inconvenient circumstances the client is enduring and are determined to create the silver lining. Instinctively, you find the positive in any situation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You jump at the opportunity to collaborate with colleagues on a project. Nothing falls through the cracks on your watch, because you diligently document progress and plan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You appreciate and thrive in a flexible work environment. You work equally well in the field, on the road, or in the office (Atlanta, Marietta). You understand that working late nights and weekends go with the territory.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You are comfortable working with large and complicated projects. Your idea of success is creating an exceptional experience for both the client and your team members, logistically solving impossible scenarios, and touching the lives of others. Your computational skills are out of this world, and your spreadsheets can easily be the difference between a good job and a great job.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You are so confident speaking on the phone, you could be giving an award acceptance speech at the Oscars or a presentation on the latest research for the cure for cancer to the world&rsquo;s leading scientists. Your people-skills make you charming, competent, and reliable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you seek fulfillment from the reassurance of others, this may not be the best fit for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You need a work history and background check that would make your mother proud. Yes, we check.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Educational Requirements</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A high school diploma is required. Any additional educational background is welcomed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Should be proficient in Office products, or similar platforms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Success will look like</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your success is measured by satisfaction scores, professional growth, accurate and timely documentation, and the ability to create relationships with clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Growth opportunities include roles such as Customer Call Center Manager, Estimator, Consultant, Project Manager and Business Development. Client fosters a learning environment and provides training to fuel growth, but the initiative belongs to you!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please note, before applying, we take hiring very seriously.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Interviewing with Client is confidential. The process includes phone and on-site interviews, and we may request a sample work product.</li>\r\n	<li>Make sure we can see where you picked up your customer service superpowers somewhere in your cover letter or resume</li>\r\n	<li>Although we are unable to follow up with each applicant, we do our best to run a thorough process for candidates with whom we identify as a potential fit</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Brief Company Overview</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Client is your dedicated disaster preparedness, response and recovery crew. We partner with businesses and communities across the southeast, offering a suite of services from assessments and training, to rapid relief, to full restoration. With a watchful eye and forward-thinking solutions, our team is always a step ahead of what&rsquo;s next and committed to safeguarding people and rebuilding lives.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Job Type: Full-time</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Experience:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Salesforce: 2 years (Preferred)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Job Location:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Marietta, GA 30066 (Preferred)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Benefits: Comprehensive&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Salary: Commensurate with experience&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Project Coordination , Executive Administrative Duties ', 82870, 0, '0', '0', '', '', 0, '2018-09-10 10:36:48', 0, 300, 347),
