ight:41px;\">\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Client is a group health insurance agency located in Johns Creek. We are one of the top independent health insurance consulting companies in the United States and work closely with our clients and their employees to create and implement their employee benefits. Our focus is businesses with less than 300 employees and Purchasing Coalitions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"right\">*Industry Specific Software</p>\r\n\r\n<p><!--![endif]----><!--![endif]----><!--![endif]----><!--![endif]----></p>\r\n', '', 82747, 0, '0', '0', '', '', 0, '2018-09-10 10:36:48', 0, 1038, 338),
(13, 'Commercial Lines Account Manager', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0', '', 648500, '', 'both', '', '', '<div>\r\n<p>Job Description-Commercial Lines Account Manager</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><b><u>Reports To</u>:</b> Commercial Lines Department Manager</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><u>Position Summary</u>:&nbsp; </b>The Account Manager manages an assigned book of business for the commercial lines department.&nbsp; This individual is an expert in the insurance industry.&nbsp; This position primarily collaborates with the Department Manager, Producers and Assistant Account Manager(s) in the agency.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><u>Responsibilities:</u></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>New Business</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Processes new business forms</li>\r\n	<li>Reviews data on insurance documents, applications, and policies</li>\r\n	<li>Assists producers with prospect/client set up in management system</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Renewals</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Identifies renewals that need marketing</li>\r\n	<li>Reviews both agency and direct bill renewals with Assistant Account Managers and Producers</li>\r\n	<li>Communicates with Producers&nbsp; proactively with renewals</li>\r\n	<li>Sends out Agency bill renewals as needed</li>\r\n	<li>Manually renews Agency Bill policies in Epic as needed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Endorsements</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Directs incoming requests to the Assistant Account Manager to process by forwarding emails, phone calls or setting up activity</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Cancellations and Reinstatements</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Corresponds with clients on cancellation requests</li>\r\n	<li>Handles reinstatement process when applicable</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Remarketing and Rewrites</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Identifies and handles remarketing opportunities</li>\r\n	<li>Identifies and handles mid-term rewrites</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Audits</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Handles Audits</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Inspections</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Reviews and Processes insurance inspections</li>\r\n	<li>Coordinates inspection requirements with clients</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Cross selling</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Identifies opportunities to round out accounts and cross sells</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Accounting</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Transacts New , Renewals, Endorsements and Cancellations when applicable</li>\r\n	<li>Sends and tracks payment invoices to clients when applicable</li>\r\n	<li>Handles Premium Finance process</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Agency Management system</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Uses computers and agency database to enter, access, and retrieve information</li>\r\n	<li>Edits, reviews and maintain records of customer&rsquo;s interactions and transactions, recording details of policies, correspondence, and inquiries</li>\r\n	<li>Utilizes Epic management system for managing all assigned work</li>\r\n	<li>Sets activities on all duties that need to be completed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Client Servicing and Communication</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Confers with customers via telephone, email, letters and in person</li>\r\n	<li>Composes business correspondence via letter and email</li>\r\n	<li>Answers all business phone calls as soon as possible, changes voice mail as needed</li>\r\n	<li>Examines documents&nbsp; and all related correspondence for completeness and accuracy</li>\r\n	<li>Obtains information from customers and maintain activity records of all interactions</li>\r\n	<li>Covers emergency duties when other Commercial Account Manager&nbsp; is out of the office</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Other duties as assigned</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><u>Knowledge, Skills and Abilities:</u></b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Must be an assertive self &ndash;starter with effective presentation skills through both verbal and written communications</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Must be able to work in a fast-paced, multi-tasking environment</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b><u>Requirements: </u></b>&nbsp;Current P&amp;C license with at least 2 years&rsquo; experience in the insurance industry</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Additional</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Work from office environment</p>\r\n\r\n<p>401K 3% match</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Medical/Dental/Vision 100% paid by employer</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Office Culture: Family friendly, office participates in civic charities, provides quarterly fun days</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Location Charleston South Carolina&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Commercial Insurance, South Carolina Insurance License, Computer and Phone work, ', 82739, 0, '0', '0', '', '', 0, '2018-09-10 10:36:48', 0, 1037, 335),
(14, 'Commercial Account Analyst', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0', '', 0, '', 'both', '', '', '<p><b>Commercial Lines Analyst Customer Service Representative </b></p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Duties</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The CSR provides support to the Commercial Account Manager unit by clearing submissions, handling endorsements, producing account Confirmation of Coverage, clearing new business, soliciting renewals, soliciting new business, setting-up, releasing and following-up on submissions and quotes and other functions as needed</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In this role, you will have the opportunity to process new business, renewals and endorsements for assigned accounts, communicate with team members and outside distributors regarding needs and account changes, maintain logs, monthly report data, record of losses, endorsements and other pertinent information.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Processing includes accurately entering all risk and exposure data into the system and following-up on binder subjectivities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Qualifications</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Georgia Property and Casualty Insurance License</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One to two years&rsquo; commercial lines experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>High School diploma required, bachelor&rsquo;s degree preferred.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Benefits Offered:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Comprehensive:&nbsp; Medical, Dental, Vision</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Salary: Commensurate with Experience&nbsp; ( Above Market)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Location: Atlanta, Georgia &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Commercial Insurance Suppport, Georgia Insurance Agents License, \r\nCustomer Service Property and Casualty Insurance ', 82697, 0, '0', '0', '', '', 0, '2018-09-10 10:36:48', 0, 549, 333),
(15, 'Property Restoration Project Manager', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0', '', 582069, '', 'both', '', '', '<p><b>Property Restoration Project Manger</b>&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Job Description</b>&nbsp;Project Manager position for a fast-growing restoration company. This is a write/run position. In this position, you will be performing daily site inspections for reconstruction and remodeling leads. You will be responsible for some of these listed: scoping, estimating, selling and overseeing the production of your assigned projects. The PM overseas all subcontractors and produces the job according to a set budget. You will be responsible for multiple projects at one time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Responsibilities</b></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Directly responsible for estimating of remodeling and reconstruction projects (Xactimate)</li>\r\n	<li>Work with the property owner and insurance company to obtain an accurate scope of work</li>\r\n	<li>Maximize customer satisfaction, revenue, growth and profitability through effective management and coordination of customer service, and promotion of all corporate goals and objectives.</li>\r\n	<li>Establish and maintain strong relationships with customers and insurance representatives.</li>\r\n	<li>Establish strong book of subcontractors to produce the job</li>\r\n	<li>Oversee the production of the job from start to finish</li>\r\n	<li>Maintain your personal job dashboard daily</li>\r\n	<li>Dispatch and coordinate subcontractor and vendor schedules and activities</li>\r\n	<li>Complete all projects on time and within budget</li>\r\n	<li>Meet monthly and quarterly goals and KPI&rsquo;s</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Candidate Requirements</b></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Minimum 2 years&rsquo; experience with Xactimate estimating software.</li>\r\n	<li>Experience in the restoration or property insurance industry</li>\r\n	<li>Effective at monitoring and managing multiple projects.</li>\r\n	<li>Emphasis on accurate project estimating.</